proliferator-activated receptor gamma (Pparg) and mouse sulfotransferase (mSTa); 
and a decrease in glucose-6-phosphatase-α (G6pc) mRNA, which might signify 
improvement of body condition. The important finding of our study was that a 
mild CR regimen, as low as 10 and 20%, was sufficient to impair glycemia in a 
non-fasted state, and also the levels of plasma IGF-1, corroborating the concept 
that mild CR has the potential for improving health and longevity, even when 
started later in life.

